e,"rule_id":"USDPA-023","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-024","rule_version":"1.0.0"},{"elapsed_ms":0,"fired":false,"rule_id":"USDPA-025","rule_version":"1.0.0"}],"findings":[{"description":"No clause allocates IP ownership of Outputs as between Customer and Vendor.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Output ownership is a frequent dispute and varies materially across vendors; allocation must be explicit.","id":"ADDENDA-013-s1-0","recommendation":"Allocate explicitly: e.g., 'As between the parties, Customer owns Outputs to the extent permitted by law; Vendor retains its models and tooling.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-013","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-ai-rmf-consensus-practice-not-statute-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST AI RMF (consensus practice, not statute)","source_url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework"}],"title":"IP ownership of AI Outputs unallocated"},{"description":"No AI-subprocessor list (named or by URL) was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"When AI features are powered by a third-party model provider, GDPR Art. 28(2) requires authorisation and disclosure.","id":"ADDENDA-015-s1-0","recommendation":"List AI subprocessors by name (e.g., OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Cohere) or reference a maintained URL.","rule_id":"ADDENDA-015","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-gdpr-article-28-2-subprocessor-authorisation-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"GDPR Article 28(2) (subprocessor authorisation)","source_url":"https://www.nist.gov/"}],"title":"AI subprocessor disclosure missing"},{"description":"No obligation to delete fine-tuning / training data on termination was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without deletion, Customer Data can persist in vendor model weights indefinitely.","id":"ADDENDA-016-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'On termination, Vendor shall delete all fine-tuning datasets derived from Customer Data within 30 days; trained model weights derived from Customer Data shall be deleted within 90 days.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-016","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-gdpr-art-17-right-to-erasure-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"GDPR Art. 17 (right to erasure)","source_url":"https://www.nist.gov/"}],"title":"Fine-tuning data deletion-on-termination missing"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a governing-law clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no governing-law clause)"},"explanation":"A governing-law clause picks the legal system that interprets the contract. Without it, courts apply conflict-of-laws rules, which may produce unexpected results.","id":"CHOICE-001-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No governing-law clause detected"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a limitation-of-liability clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no LoL clause)"},"explanation":"Without a limitation-of-liability clause, exposure is bounded only by what the parties can prove in damages. Most commercial contracts cap liability.","id":"RISK-005-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No limitation-of-liability clause detected"},{"description":"Used but not defined: Customer Data.","document_position":558,"excerpt":{"end_offset":571,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":558,"text":"Customer Data"},"explanation":"Title-Case phrases in a contract usually signal a defined term. When they aren't defined, readers must guess at the intended meaning. Either define them or use lowercase if the term is intended in its ordinary sense.","id":"STRUCT-006-s1-558","recommendation":"Add a definition for each genuinely defined term, or change the casing if the phrase is being used in its ordinary sense.","rule_id":"STRUCT-006","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Undefined Title-Case terms: 1"},{"description":"The survival clause exists but does not name: indemnification.","document_position":1098,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1660,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1098,"text":"2. Prohibition on Training on Customer Data. Vendor shall not use Customer Data, including any derived or transformed forms thereof, to train, fine-tune, retrain, improve, or otherwise modify any AI model, including Vendor's proprietary models or any third-party foundational mode"},"explanation":"Survival language is what keeps sticky obligations alive after a contract terminates. A survival clause that doesn't expressly enumerate the present-in-document confidentiality / IP / indemnity obligations creates ambiguity at the moment those obligations matter most — post-termination, when the contract has already ended.","id":"TEMP-012-s1-1098","recommendation":"Add explicit named references to the missing obligation(s): indemnification. Standard drafting names every sticky section by number or category in the survival clause.","rule_id":"TEMP-012","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival clause does not name 1 sticky obligation"},{"description":"The contract does not state a path to terminate for material breach.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no for-cause termination)"},"explanation":"Without a for-cause termination path, parties must rely on common-law material-breach doctrines, which are jurisdiction-dependent.","id":"TERM-002-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No termination-for-cause clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not state what happens upon termination.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no effect-of-termination clause)"},"explanation":"An effect-of-termination clause spells out the rights and obligations that survive, the return or destruction of materials, and the wind-down rules.","id":"TERM-005-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-005","rule_version":"1.2.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No effect-of-termination clause detected"},{"description":"No hallucination-risk acknowledgment or human-review obligation for high-stakes outputs was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Practitioner posture is: AI outputs are not fit for legal / medical / financial advice without human review.","id":"ADDENDA-014-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Outputs are provided as-is and may contain inaccuracies; Customer is responsible for human review prior to use for legal, medical, or financial decisions.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-014","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-ai-rmf-consensus-practice-not-statute-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST AI RMF (consensus practice, not statute)","source_url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework"}],"title":"AI hallucination disclaimer / human-review obligation missing"},{"description":"The document does not state where disputes must be brought.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no venue clause)"},"explanation":"Without a venue clause, default venue rules apply (in federal court, 28 U.S.C. § 1391). A clear forum-selection clause avoids ambiguity.","id":"CHOICE-003-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-003","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-28-usc-1391","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"28 U.S.C. § 1391 (venue generally)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/28/1391"}],"title":"No venue / forum clause detected"},{"description":"The contract references data but does not separately allocate data ownership.","document_position":558,"excerpt":{"end_offset":571,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":558,"text":"This Artificial Intelligence Use Addendum (\"AI Addendum\") is entered into as of March 1, 2026, by and between Stark Enterprises LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (\"Customer\"), and Wayne Analytics Inc., a California corporation (\"Ven"},"explanation":"IP and data ownership are different. For SaaS, the customer typically owns its data; the vendor typically owns usage analytics. Address each explicitly.","id":"IPDATA-004-s1-558","rule_id":"IPDATA-004","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Data ownership not separately addressed"},{"description":"Only vendor bears this typically-mutual obligation.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"indemnification obligation"},"explanation":"Obligations like confidentiality, indemnity, and representations are usually mutual. A one-sided version is sometimes intentional but worth confirming.","id":"OBLI-002-s1-0","rule_id":"OBLI-002","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Asymmetric indemnification obligation"},{"description":"Vendor shall not use Customer Data, including any derived or transformed forms thereof, to train, fine-tune, retrain, im | Vendor shall not subject any Customer Data to AI processing unless Customer has affirmatively opted in to such processin","document_position":1142,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1380,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1142,"text":"Vendor shall not use Customer Data, including any derived or transformed forms thereof, to train, fine-tune, retrain, improve, or otherwise modify any AI model, including Vendor's proprietary models or any third-party foundational model."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-1142","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 2"},{"description":"Indemnity clause appears to be missing: defense control, settlement consent.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"6. Vendor Indemnity for AI-Generated IP Infringement. Vendor shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Customer and its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims, damages, losses, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorney"},"explanation":"A complete indemnity clause specifies (a) the timeline and form for notice of a claim, (b) which party controls defense, and (c) whether settlement requires consent.","id":"RISK-011-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-011","rule_version":"1.3.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Indemnity procedural elements missing: defense control, settlement consent"},{"description":"Infringement. Vendor shall indemnif","document_position":3097,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3132,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3097,"text":"6. Vendor Indemnity for AI-Generated IP Infringement. Vendor shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Customer and its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims, damages, losses, costs, and expenses (including reasonable attorney"},"explanation":"IP indemnity protects against third-party infringement claims. Standard scope is third-party claims only; broader scope shifts more risk to the indemnifying party.","id":"RISK-012-s1-3097","rule_id":"RISK-012","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"IP indemnity present"},{"description":"The following defined terms are never used outside their definition: NIST AI RMF.","document_position":4368,"excerpt":{"end_offset":4383,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":4368,"text":"NIST AI RMF"},"explanation":"Defined terms that are not used downstream may be inherited from a template and obsolete. They clutter the contract and can confuse readers; either delete them or use them where intended.","id":"STRUCT-005-s1-4368","recommendation":"Review each unused term and either delete it or wire it into the relevant clause.","rule_id":"STRUCT-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Defined terms with no uses: 1"},{"description":"Provisions are stated to survive termination.","document_position":1610,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1634,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1610,"text":"2. Prohibition on Training on Customer Data. Vendor shall not use Customer Data, including any derived or transformed forms thereof, to train, fine-tune, retrain, improve, or otherwise modify any AI model, including Vendor's proprietary mod"},"explanation":"A survival clause names the obligations that outlast termination — typically confidentiality, indemnity, payment obligations accrued before termination, and choice of law.","id":"TEMP-006-s1-1610","rule_id":"TEMP-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival clause present"},{"description":"Survival clause does not appear to include: confidentiality, indemnity, payment, governing law.","document_position":1610,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1634,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1610,"text":"2. Prohibition on Training on Customer Data. Vendor shall not use Customer Data, including any derived or transformed forms thereof, to train, fine-tune, retrain, improve, or otherwise modify any AI model, including Vendor's proprietary mod"},"explanation":"Typical surviving obligations include confidentiality, indemnity, accrued payment obligations, and governing law. Missing any of these is common and worth confirming.","id":"TEMP-007-s1-1610","rule_id":"TEMP-007","rule_version":"1.2.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Survival list may be missing categories: confidentiality, indemnity, payment, governing law"}],"playbook_id":"ai-addendum","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to ai-addendum","result_hash":"760b1bcc04b73279d4d64d6f743ae2d1c0c1e1e4d44ff042e723f8cd42e29842","source_file":{"name":"ai-addendum-missing-hallucination-and-human-review-fail.txt","sha256":"d4c198fd68cc66c73a2c29c939688a8a840f8515b8f2fee0c6fc7bc93847e1c9","size_bytes":1},"version":"9.41.0"}